-> Unix = base of all OS's
    -> developed in 1970 by Dennis Retchie, Ken Thompson at AT&T Laboratories
    -> meant for programmers developing software
    -> Unix and C = founded by AT&T
    -> Kernel
    
    
System Structure of Linux:
    Layer 1: Hardware
    Layer 2: Kernel = interacts with hardware and tasks like memory management, task scheduling, and management
    Layer 3: Shell Commands = utility that processes requests.
      -> shell interprets commands and calls programs that we want
    Layer 4: outermost layer that executes external applications
    
    
    
